As a Python Developer Trainee, you will work closely with our development team to learn and apply Python programming skills to build and maintain software applications. You will be trained in developing web applications, working with APIs, and solving real-world problems using Python. This role is designed to provide you with the skills, tools, and hands-on experience to become a proficient Python developer.

Key Responsibilities

Assist in developing and maintaining Python-based applications and software solutions.
Write clean, efficient, and well-documented Python code.
Learn and apply Python libraries and frameworks (such as Django, Flask, Pandas, etc.).
Assist in integrating APIs and third-party services with Python applications.
Collaborate with senior developers to design, develop, and deploy software solutions.
Participate in code reviews and receive constructive feedback to improve coding skills.
Troubleshoot and debug issues in code, as well as optimize performance.
Learn version control systems (e.g., Git) and contribute to collaborative development workflows.
Assist in testing applications and implementing unit tests to ensure the functionality of code.
Participate in daily stand-ups and team meetings in a remote setting.

Qualifications

A strong interest in software development and Python programming.
Basic understanding of Python programming concepts and syntax.
Knowledge of basic web technologies (HTML, CSS, JavaScript) is a plus.
Familiarity with working in a Git-based version control environment is a bonus.
A keen problem-solving mindset with a desire to learn and improve.
Strong communication skills, both written and verbal.
Ability to work independently and as part of a remote team.
Enthusiasm for continuous learning and adapting to new technologies.

Preferred Skills

Familiarity with Python web frameworks like Django or Flask.
Basic experience with databases (SQL or NoSQL).
Knowledge of RESTful API development and integration.
Familiarity with data structures, algorithms, and object-oriented programming.
Exposure to cloud platforms or containerization (e.g., AWS, Docker) is a bonus.
Previous internship or academic experience in Python development is a plus.

Why Join Us?

Gain hands-on experience working with experienced developers on real-world projects.
Opportunity to enhance your Python programming skills and broaden your development knowledge.
Flexible remote work environment.
Mentorship from senior developers and a collaborative team atmosphere.
Competitive compensation for trainees with the possibility of full-time employment after successful completion of the trainee period.
Opportunities for career advancement and skill development.
